item.title: Compiling errors
item.dc:creator: @Yz85Racer Yz85Racer
item.description:
@Yz85Racer wrote:

[quote=“Sledge, post:17, topic:134095”]I’m not building, just editing…

So what do you suggest I do? is there a way to incorporate other class files into the main one so there’s no need for importing?[/quote]
Extend it?
Or, make a directory, and put the files you want to include in your main file. Call it say, “Includes”, then at the top of all the files in your new directory, put
package Includes.filesToInc;
Then in the main file, import Includes.filesToInc;

item.title: Compiling errors
item.dc:creator: @mod_taharok Taharok
item.description:
@mod_taharok wrote:

You can’t import resources from the direct classpath, there really is no point to doing so. Import is for including class files in other directories that are packaged.

If you did not know what I just said, you might want to learn more about Java before building larger projects such as games.

item.title: Compiling errors
item.dc:creator: @imafatmess imafatmess
item.description:
@imafatmess wrote:

The source is the java files, java files are compiled into class files (with ease) then can be decompiled back to java files (harder). When java files are obfuscated then compiled (into class files) it is much hardert to decompile the file (into a java file) and make it understandable, etc… Also, have you installed java?
